  "tips": [
    "It is a small waterfall compared to that of the Cinca, but of great beauty.",
    "A great view of the surrounding peaks, such as La Munia and Monte Perdido.",
    "A nice leisurely hike, particularly good as an introduction to the big hiking tours. At about 1,400 m you pass a smaller waterfall with red-brown rock formations.\r\nThe La Larri waterfall falls about 180 m with a roaring sound.\r\nBehind the mountain range is France and from here you can climb to the peak of La Munia."
